{"type":"compaction","id":"04528c10","parentId":"fb2c06ab","timestamp":"2026-04-07T08:51:55.932Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Write a comprehensive analysis article about Specification-Driven Development (SDD)\n- Target audience: technical managers and development teams\n- Analyze SDD's development history, methodologies, essence, limitations, and its role in the AI era\n- Collect and analyze major SDD tools/frameworks and big tech company practices\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- No team-specific case studies needed\n- Need to collect big tech company practices\n- Macro perspective on SDD's evolution, strengths, and weaknesses\n- Particularly focus on how to view SDD in today's AI development environment\n- Need to correct initial misconception: SDD = Specification-Driven Development (not Speculation-Driven Development)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Initial research with broad SDD methodology coverage (though some connections were later questioned)\n- [x] Collected detailed information on modern AI-era SDD tools: Spec Kit, Superpowers, OpenSpec, Kiro\n- [x] Assembled big tech company practices using various SDD methodologies\n- [x] Created research notes and draft article (sdd-article.md)\n- [x] Submitted draft for review, received feedback about questionable methodology lineage\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Re-evaluating the development lineage section based on user feedback\n- [ ] Considering how to properly categorize methodologies that have tangential relationships to SDD\n\n### Blocked\n- [User questioned whether certain methodologies properly belong in SDD's development history]\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Main SDD Lineage**: Formal methods → Design by Contract → TDD/BDD/SbE → AI-era tools (Spec Kit/OpenSpec/Superpowers/Kiro)\n- **Questionable Inclusions**: API-First, Contract Testing, Property-Based Testing, Type-Driven Development may be incorrectly categorized as SDD evolution\n- **Correction Needed**: Must distinguish between true SDD lineage and methodologies that only tangentially relate to specifications\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Re-evaluate and revise the \"SDD Development History\" section to only include methodologies with direct SDD lineage\n2. Move methodologies like API-First, Contract Testing, PBT to a separate section discussing \"Related but Distinct Practices\"\n3. Strengthen the article with better sourcing for methodology connections\n4. Address user's concern about over-categorization in the revised version\n\n## Critical Context\n- SDD article draft exists at `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md`\n- Research notes at `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-research.md`\n- User specifically questioned the methodology lineage in the \"SDD Development History\" section\n- Need to maintain macro perspective while ensuring accurate methodology categorization\n- Must preserve the article's core analysis on SDD in AI era while fixing historical lineage issues\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user shared a detailed conversation between themselves and an AI assistant about Specification-Driven Development (SDD). The conversation included an extensive exploration of SDD's evolution through different eras, with the AI assistant subsequently editing an article about SDD based on insights gained.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The conversation traced SDD's evolution from formal methods in the 1960s-80s through contract-driven development in the 1990s-2000s, API-first approaches in the 2010s, and finally to AI-era tools.\n- The AI assistant was then editing an article about SDD, making revisions to:\n  1. Incorporate the \"from aristocratic to平民化\" (democratization) narrative\n  2. Remove PBT, TypeDD, and MBT from the main SDD development lineage and position them as related but distinct practices\n  3. Clarify the positioning of API-First/Contract Testing within the SDD spectrum\n  4. Refine the overall tone to be more historically rigorous\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe retained suffix shows the AI assistant continuing to edit the SDD article, specifically:\n- Making changes to distinguish SDD's direct lineage from related practices\n- Adding a new section to explain Property-Based Testing (PBT), Type-Driven Development (TypeDD), and Model-Based Testing (MBT) as methodologies that intersect with SDD but have different core philosophies\n- Updating the \"Big Company Practices\" table to reflect these distinctions\n- Emphasizing that the key differentiator of SDD is its \"spec-first\" philosophy, not merely the use of formal expressions\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/BOOTSTRAP.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/MEMORY.md\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-research.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"add4b6e3","tokensBefore":117478,"details":{"readFiles":["/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/BOOTSTRAP.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/MEMORY.md","/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md","/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-research.md"]},"fromHook":false}
