{"type":"message","id":"a260f60a","parentId":"b632b0ec","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:04:52.460Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f83478afdae042349b8da94c","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Kiro AWS spec-driven development review comparison 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"tookMs\": 11328,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07d4ee157a52fe1b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro Review 2026: Amazon's Spec-Driven AI Agent That Codes for Days\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07d4ee157a52fe1b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.heyuan110.com/posts/ai/2026-03-10-kiro-review/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0a35577902d513a5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIn-depth review of Amazon Kiro IDE — the spec-driven AI coding agent with Agent Hooks, Steering Files, and MCP support. Plus the AWS outage incident and lessons learned.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0a35577902d513a5\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.heyuan110.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"50835f5835e9abca\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nI Tested the Top Spec-Driven Dev Tools in 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"50835f5835e9abca\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://dev.to/filiksyos/i-tested-the-top-spec-driven-dev-tools-in-2026-4gdm\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f2539686c4064618\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro (by AWS ) Kiro is AWS's answer to spec-driven development . Launched mid-2025, it's a full VS Code fork, not just an extension bolted onto the side. What it actually does: You've got two modes—vibe mode if you're just prototyping, and spec mode when you want structure. In spec mode, Kiro spits out user stories with acceptance criteria, a design doc, and a task list. You iterate on all ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f2539686c4064618\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dev.to\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5f6ccc215543e1fd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro Review: Amazon's Spec-Driven IDE Powered by Claude\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5f6ccc215543e1fd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.openaitoolshub.org/en/blog/kiro-review-amazon-ide\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3eb79659ae5ef974\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAmazon Kiro is a spec-driven IDE that turns requirements into working code using Claude Sonnet. Free tier gives 50 interactions per month. Here is a hands-on look at spec -first development , how it compares to Cursor, and whether it survived \\\"bringing down AWS \\\".\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3eb79659ae5ef974\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.openaitoolshub.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"62ff9fc9866428e6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nI Tested AWS Kiro For One Month And Here Is What Nobody Tells You\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"62ff9fc9866428e6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://kearai.com/agents/kiro-ai-review-aws-agentic-ide-guide\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"363e4dab52c2f7bc\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA comprehensive Kiro AI review based on real-world experience. Discover how AWS's spec-driven agentic IDE compares to Cursor and Windsurf, including pricing, features, EARS methodology, and honest ins...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"363e4dab52c2f7bc\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"kearai.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a6249973cc31cac0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro AI: AWS Spec-Driven IDE | Review 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a6249973cc31cac0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.comparateur-ia-facile.com/en/kiro-ai\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"385163ebb5f3f16c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAbout Kiro AI Kiro is the AI IDE developed by Amazon Web Services ( AWS ), launched in July 2025. Its philosophy is radically different from other AI IDEs: rather than simply \\\"vibe coding\\\" without structure, Kiro enforces a spec-driven workflow that formalizes the AI-assisted development process.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"385163ebb5f3f16c\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.comparateur-ia-facile.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"46310103ed2e0109\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro Review (2026): Pricing, Features, Pros and Cons\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"46310103ed2e0109\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://vibecoding.app/blog/kiro-review\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8eda5c98dd7dd1f4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro is AWS's spec-driven AI IDE that turns prompts into requirements, design artifacts, and executable tasks. It is strongest for solo founders and indie developers who want speed without losing structure. Standout features are spec workflows, agent hooks, and better project continuity. Main tradeoff: for quick solo hacking, Kiro can feel heavier than lightweight vibe-coding tools.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8eda5c98dd7dd1f4\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"vibecoding.app\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"57249792ae236863\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nKiro Cheat Sheets & Comparisons - Ship AI-ready code faster\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"57249792ae236863\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://kiro.directory/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e72e28765ab21680\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAll the AWS Kiro tips, specs & comparisons in one place. Master spec-driven development , hooks automation, and compare Kiro with Copilot, Cursor, and more.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e72e28765ab21680\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"kiro.directory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"eabe8c5568f4b939\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSpec-Driven Development Tools Comparison - GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"eabe8c5568f4b939\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/cameronsjo/spec-compare\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4bffb4752678e9bd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA comprehensive research and comparison of spec-driven development (SDD) tools for AI-assisted coding, including analysis of git worktree support, architectural approaches, and practical recommendations.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4bffb4752678e9bd\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a06acaf6c955cdf7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nUnderstanding Spec-Driven-Development: Kiro, spec-kit, and Tessl\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a06acaf6c955cdf7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://martinfowler.com/articles/exploring-gen-ai/sdd-3-tools.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"44ec29e84491f266\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWho is the target user? Many of the demos and tutorials for spec-driven development tools include things like defining product and feature goals, they even incorporate terms like \\\"user story\\\". The idea here might be to use AI as an enabler for cross-skilling, and have developers participate more heavily in requirements analysis?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"44ec29e84491f266\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"martinfowler.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\"