{"type":"compaction","id":"9ed3debd","parentId":"c166eabe","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:16:47.895Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Write a comprehensive analysis article about Specification-Driven Development (SDD)\n- Target audience: technical managers and development teams\n- Analyze SDD's development history, methodologies, essence, limitations, and its role in the AI era\n- Collect and analyze major SDD tools/frameworks and big tech company practices\n- **Chapter 2 must be rewritten**: replace methodology taxonomy with AI-era SDD tool practice comparison + big tech company SDD practices (especially Chinese companies: Alibaba, ByteDance, Meituan)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- No team-specific case studies needed\n- Need to collect big tech company practices, especially domestic (Chinese) ones\n- Macro perspective on SDD's evolution, strengths, and weaknesses\n- Focus on how to view SDD in today's AI development environment\n- SDD = Specification-Driven Development\n- User says article \"整体有点空\" (feels empty overall) — needs more substance, especially in Chapter 2\n- Chapter 2 should NOT be a deeper methodology taxonomy dive — it should be practical tool comparison + real company cases\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Initial research with broad SDD methodology coverage\n- [x] Collected detailed information on modern AI-era SDD tools: Spec Kit, Superpowers, OpenSpec, Kiro\n- [x] Assembled big tech company practices using various SDD methodologies\n- [x] Created research notes and draft article (sdd-article.md)\n- [x] Revised SDD development lineage — distinguished direct lineage from related practices (PBT, TypeDD, MBT moved to separate section)\n- [x] Fixed duplicate table rows in big company practices table\n- [x] Removed PBT over-categorization from executability and participant sections\n- [x] Added standard citations [1]-[21] throughout the article\n- [x] Added `## 参考来源` section at end with 21 references (books, papers, official sites, GitHub repos)\n- [x] Fixed duplicate paragraph in section 1.4 (\"这催生了 AI 原生的 SDD 工具浪潮\" appeared twice)\n- [x] Extensive web research for Chapter 2 rewrite materials collected\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Rewrite Chapter 2** — Replace \"方法论图谱\" with \"AI 时代的 SDD 工具生态与工程实践\" containing tool comparison + big tech cases\n- [ ] Commit the Chapter 2 rewrite\n\n### Blocked\n- [ ] Edit tool requires `oldText` parameter — large section replacement needs to use exact old text match or alternative approach\n- [ ] Bing and Google search engines blocked (captcha/empty results); only DuckDuckGo works\n- [ ] Toutiao article (JS-rendered) and WeChat article content could not be fetched; Aliyun article only returned abstract\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Main SDD Lineage**: Formal methods → Design by Contract → TDD/BDD/SbE → AI-era tools\n- **Questionable Inclusions moved**: API-First, Contract Testing, PBT, TypeDD, MBT positioned as related but distinct\n- **Chapter 2 restructure**: User explicitly said Chapter 2 should be tool practices/comparison + big tech cases, NOT deeper methodology taxonomy\n- **Chinese big tech focus**: User specifically requested Alibaba, ByteDance, Meituan SDD practice articles\n- **Chapter 2 boundaries**: Lines 96-178 in sdd-article.md (from `## 二、...` to before `## 三、SDD 的本质`)\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Replace Chapter 2 (lines 96-178) with new content using the edit tool with exact oldText matching\n2. New Chapter 2 structure should include:\n   - AI-era SDD tool ecosystem overview (Spec Kit, Superpowers, OpenSpec, Kiro, GSD, Taskmaster AI)\n   - Tool comparison table (workflow, philosophy, strengths/weaknesses)\n   - Big tech SDD practices: overseas (GitHub Spec Kit, Amazon TLA+, Stripe API-First) + domestic (Alibaba multi-AI SDD with OpenSpec for cross-border insurance, etc.)\n   - Reference the arxiv paper's three-level SDD spectrum (spec-first / spec-anchored / spec-as-source)\n   - Include the contrarian WeChat article perspective (\"谨防 Spec Driven Development 它不是银弹\")\n3. Update reference numbers if new citations are added\n4. Git commit after rewrite\n\n## Critical Context\n- Article file: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md`\n- Research notes: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-research.md`\n- Chapter 2 spans lines 96-178 (verified via `grep -n \"^## \"`)\n- Chapter structure: 引言(L5) → 一(L19) → 二(L96) → 三(L179) → 四(L231) → 五(L283) → 结语(L377) → 参考来源(L395)\n- Collected research materials for Chapter 2:\n  - **arxiv paper** (2602.00180v1): SDD three-level spectrum, academic definition\n  - **ThoughtWorks blog**: SDD as 2025 key engineering practice, spec vs PRD distinction\n  - **Spillwave article**: GSD vs Spec Kit vs OpenSpec vs Taskmaster AI deep comparison\n  - **johng.cn**: OpenSpec engineering practice with Claude Code, CLAUDE.md constraints, custom Skills\n  - **Zhihu/Aliyun article**: Multi-AI collaborative SDD (Claude+Codex+Gemini) for cross-border insurance\n  - **Tencent Cloud article**: SDD tutorial-style content (lower quality)\n  - **WeChat \"古法编程研究所\"**: \"谨防 Spec Driven Development 它不是银弹\" (title only, contrarian view)\n  - **OpenSpec official site**: SDD definition, why it matters for AI coding\n  - **Spec Kit GitHub**: Official spec-driven.md with \"Code is no longer king\" manifesto\n  - **Superpowers guide (tinyash.com)**: 5-step workflow, Skills system details\n- User-provided links that partially worked:\n  - `https://www.toutiao.com/article/7602090913594114596` — could not fetch (JS-rendered)\n  - `https://cloud.tencent.com/developer/article/2648323` — fetched but low quality\n  - `https://developer.aliyun.com/article/1708977` — only abstract\n  - `https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/GsgPv0zivy8KbiJ0WsAK4w` — title only: \"谨防 Spec Driven Development 它不是银弹\"\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user shared a WeChat article link and asked the assistant to review it.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant read the existing Chapter 2 (lines 96-177) of `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md`, which was titled \"二、方法论图谱：SDD 的直接谱系与相关实践\" and covered methodology taxonomy across 4 dimensions plus related practices and a big-company practice table.\n- The assistant replaced the entire Chapter 2 with a completely rewritten version titled \"二、AI 时代的 SDD 工具生态与工程实践\", incorporating content apparently informed by the shared article. The new chapter covers: a \"spec spectrum\" framework (Spec-First/Anchored/as-Source), a comparison table of 4 mainstream SDD tools (Spec Kit, OpenSpec, Superpowers, GSD), domestic engineering practices (4 case studies from Aliyun, johng.cn, Tencent Cloud, and a critical voice), and an expanded big-company practice table with spec spectrum positions.\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The file being edited is `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md`\n- The replacement edit was confirmed successful\n- The assistant was verifying the edit by re-reading from line 96, confirming the new chapter content starts correctly\n- The new Chapter 2 is substantially longer than the old one (355+ lines from offset 98 onward), which may affect line numbers for subsequent chapters\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/BOOTSTRAP.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/MEMORY.md\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md\n/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-research.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"e208bcd0","tokensBefore":139942,"details":{"readFiles":["/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/BOOTSTRAP.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/MEMORY.md","/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md","/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-research.md"]},"fromHook":false}
